cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with information theory and communication in wireless networks, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The use of a relay node and the study of the achievable rate region also suggest that it could belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also involves probabilistic graphs, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The study of the joint distribution of $p_{XY}$ suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the use of inner and outer bounds suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
